text.tspan: Foam board for each kid (as a build platform)
Stack of "rocket part" cards for each kid (with plenty of replacements for trial-and-error)
Stack of Ozocode stickers for each kid

flowRoot.flowPara: 1. Instructor explains the goal is to "build each rocket part" by having the Evo trace the part
2. Kids will need to place Ozocodes to ensure the Evo traces the entire part
3. Each kid is given a single card at a time, and a volunteer watches once they indicate that they're ready to test
4. If the part was fully traced, the kid receives the next rocket part card
5. Once all the parts are built, the rocket part cards put together will create a rocket - VICTORY!
IDEA: to make it harder, every few minutes make every kid randomly draw an Ozocode - now they have to integrate that Ozocode into the part they're building right now
